<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Burnley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-11-30"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 30, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of yesterday’s date, and of its enclosures,
                            relative to the alleged existence of a military organization in Canada
                            of fugitives from the United States.</p>
                        <p>I have this day transmitted copies of the note, and of its enclosures, to
                            his excellency the governor general of Canada.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>For LORD LYONS,</signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <signed>J. HUME BURNLEY.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>